2 mins breakfast recipe 😮 Ready to Eat 😆

Upma premix. 

Some pro tips- 
Upma premix is always there in my refrigerator. 
You can carry it to office, travel, hostel.

Ingredients:

For Upma Mix:
- 1 kg sooji or rawa (semolina)
- 1 cup roasted peanuts
- 4 tablespoons ghee
- 2 tablespoons mustard seeds
- 1-2 hari mirch (green chilli)
- 2 teaspoons urad dal (split black gram)
- 2 teaspoons chana dal (split chickpea lentils)
- 20-25 kari patta (curry leaves)
- Dhaniya (coriander leaves)
- Salt to taste
- 20-25 chopped kaju (cashew)

Instructions:

1. Take a pan and add sooji 
2. Dry roast until half done 
3. Now add dhaniya and dry roast until the sooji turns aromatic and slightly golden. 

For tadka 

1. Heat 4 tablespoons of ghee in a large pan over medium heat.

2. Add chana dal, peanuts, urad dal, hari mirch, kari patta, mustard seeds and kaju. Sauté until the dal turns golden brown and the mustard seeds splutter.

4. Now add salt as per taste.

4. Add the dry roasted sooji and roast it on medium-low heat while stirring continuously for 2 min. Be careful not to burn it.

4. Remove the roasted sooji from the pan and let it cool completely.

5. Once cooled, Transfer the mixture to an airtight container.

This instant upma mix can be stored in an airtight container for several weeks, making it a convenient option for quick breakfast or snacks.

Your instant upma mix is ready!

To Make Upma Using the Mix:

1. Take upma mix in a container
2. Add equivalent amount of water
3. Close the lid for 5 min. 
4. You can micro it for 2 min if needed. 
4. Upma is ready to eat. 

You can also make it in a saucepan by adding your choice of vegetables like onion, bell peppers, peas.

🛑Not buying a swiss travel pass if you plan to visit multiple museums & places. Many places like titlis, matterhorn and grindelwald are 50% off with swiss pass
🛑Not checking WEBCAMS before visiting the mountains. ensure to check the webcam on the official website to decide if it’s worth visiting or better reschedule
🛑If you are going to the mountains, make sure you take extra layers with you as it gets really chilly on top
🛑 Always use washroom on station /trains as those are free
🛑 Not carrying reffilable water bottles. You can fill water from any tap apart from the once clearly mentioned not good for drinking.
🛑Buses and trains stop on request on smaller stops so remember to press the stop button if you have to get down on a small stop
🛑Buy snacks or bakery from stores like coop and migros as they are much cheaper and have many ready to eat options also
🛑Always carry your passport if you are traveling in train. The TC sometimes checks the passport as well alongwith the swiss pass
🛑Make sure you don’t keep legs on the front chair in train as you can end up paying a fine
🛑Always check the class 1 or 2 before you enter the train coach so that you get into the right class coach for which you have bought the tickets
🛑Always try to go on mountains as early as possible as it is not crowded in the morning (especially at mount titlis post 10 it gets very crowded)
🛑Always carry food and water bottles while going to mountians as food is expensive at the restaurants up there
🛑Brought wrong currency - switzerland uses the swiss franc, not the euro
🛑Buying the wrong power plug.
Switzerland uses type C & J plugs, and anything else won’t work without a universal adapter.
